HEADWORD: Godship
<hw>God"ship</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>God</ets>, n. +
<ets>-ship</ets>.]</ety> <def>The rank or character of a god; deity;
divinity; a god or goddess.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O'er hills and dales their <qex>godships</qex> came.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

